Japan's Reckless Anti-DPRK Racket Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries' reckless moves to apply sanctions against the DPRK and put pressure on it only escalate their confrontation with the DPRK and drive the situation on the Korean peninsula to a grave phase. Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These moves of Japan diametrically run counter to the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration in which both sides committed themselves to observe international law and stop doing anything threatening the security of the other side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are getting evermore zealous in their moves to lay an international siege to the DPRK, pursuant to the U.S. hostile policy toward it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have become more clamorous for economic sanctions at a time when the U.S. is set to stage five multinational exercises this year to lay an international siege to the DPRK. This is not just an accidental coincidence. Lurking behind the Japanese reactionaries' clamour for sanctions against the DPRK and pressure on it, is a sinister aim to fish in troubled waters, pursuant to the U.S. hostile policy toward it. It is their true intention to escalate the hostile moves against the DPRK and bring down its socialist system in line with the U.S. imperialists' policy to tighten the economic sanctions against Pyongyang and increase pressure upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK clarified more than once that it would regard any sanctions and blockade against it as a declaration of a war and would take corresponding measures for self-defence. However, the Japanese reactionaries are openly seeking to escalate sanctions and pressure against the DPRK. This can not be construed otherwise than a revelation of their deliberate and premeditated provocation intended to push the DPRK-Japan relations of confrontation to an extreme pitch of tension and launch a new war on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that if a war breaks out on the Korean peninsula it will spill over into Japan close to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should bear in mind that they will meet inescapable consequences if they continue acting under the pulls and pressures of the U.S., their master, without any political principle and following its policy of sanctions and pressure against the DPRK.

Anti-war Rally in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A large anti-war rally of over 5,000 citizens and students was held in Seoul on March 20, one year after the start of the U.S. war of aggression on Iraq.
 Permanent representative of the National People's Solidarity Jong Kwang Hun, Chairman of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions Ri Su Ho, Chairman of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils Paek Jong Ho and others, addressing the rally, said that lurking behind the curtain of the additional troop dispatch to Iraq is a sinister plot of the U.S. and that the U.S. is seeking to unleash the second Iraqi war in the Korean peninsula, extremely aggravating inter-Korean showdown and tension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded that the south Korean authorities immediately withdraw the disgraceful motion on additional troop dispatch to Iraq and all the U.S. troops go out of this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the rally noted that the U.S. is working hard to materialize its strategy for world supremacy under the pretext of guarantee for lives of young people in this land and that they would not stop their struggle before the plan for additional troop dispatch is cancelled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the rally the People's Action against the Troop Dispatch and the preparatory committee for the Joint Action against War and for Peace conducted an all-people signature campaign against the troop dispatch to Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the rally the attendants staged a demonstration on march, distributing copies of literature among citizens.

Letter of Protest Sent to U.S. President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A letter of protest to the U.S. president was published on March 19 by the Khabarovsk Territorial Association of Korean Nationals in Russia denouncing the United States and the south Korean authorities for staging large-scale war maneuvers.
 The letter noted that the large-scale RSOI and Foal Eagle joint military exercises underway in south Korea are, to all intents and purposes, saber rattling aimed to make a preemptive nuclear strike at the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. already worked out a new nuclear war scenario titled "new operation plan 5026" and is perpetrating ceaseless aerial espionage against the northern half of Korea with strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes with different missions involved in order to put its war scenario into practice. The war maneuvers launched by it are designed to unleash a war of aggression on the Korean peninsula again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the United States ignites another Korean war, it will be held wholly responsible for its ensuing consequences, the letter warned.

