U.S. Sabre Rattling against DPRK Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- Rallies were held at the Pyongyang Thermal-Power Complex and Pyongyang College of Computer Technology yesterday to condemn the anti-DPRK war moves of the U.S. war maniacs.
 A statement of the spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland was read out at the rally at the complex to be followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said that the RSOI and Foal Eagle joint military exercises launched by the U.S. and the south Korean warmongers are nothing but a test nuclear war and a preliminary war against the DPRK as they are aimed to make a preemptive attack on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They bitterly assailed the warmongers for recklessly working to provoke a new war that would bring a horrible nuclear holocaust to the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. imperialists unleash a war of aggression at last, the Korean people will wipe out the aggressors to the last one with the invincible power built up under the banner of Songun and honorably defend the dignity and security of the nation, they stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At a rally held on the education ground of the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War, students of Pyongyang College of Computer Technology on behalf of all the youth and students vehemently denounced the frantic nuclear war maneuvers launched by the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops as an open military provocation to deprive the students of the DPRK of their opportunity to study and quell the beautiful dream of the youth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, students of Pyongyang University of Medicine had a similar rally in front of the U.S. imperialists' armed spy ship "Pueblo" on March 24.

Correct Settlement of Issue Related to "Comfort Women" Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- The participants in the 600th Tokyo Wednesday demonstration for the settlement of the issue related to the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army sent a written request titled "We demand the earliest possible solution to the issue related to the 'comfort women'" to the prime minister and the foreign minister of Japan on March 17. The demonstration was staged in response to the call of 17 organizations of Japan including the "Peace Boat."
 Saying that the "comfort women" system enforced by the imperial Japanese army was a sexual slavery system based on discrimination against women and other nation as it was sponsored by the state of Japan, the written request denounced this as a violation of various international laws and crimes for which it should pay reparation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fundamental principle for the settlement of the issue related to "comfort women" for the Japanese army is to restore the dignity and honor of the victims with the state responsibility and pay state reparation to them, it said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The assertion that the issue related to the "comfort women" came to an end despite the demand of the aged victims means causing double and treble damage to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It strongly demanded the Japanese government sincerely undertake the work to relieve the victims of the state-sponsored crimes of their sufferings and take measures based on the state responsibility.

Withdrawal of "Motion on Impeachment" Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A statement was issued on March 17 by the General Association of Koreans in China in protest against the passage of the "motion on impeachment against the president" through the south Korean "National Assembly".
 The passage of the "motion on impeachment" through the NA was a political rebellion staged by a handful of political quacks in quest of their party interests, in disregard of the will of the people, the statement noted, adding that it glaringly revealed the backwardness of south Korean politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the United States is to blame for this, the statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. manipulation of the right-wing conservative forces of south Korea to hatch a plot for "impeachment" dates back to October last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We bitterly denounce such political gangsterism committed by the "Grand National Party" and conservative forces in south Korea, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
servants of the U.S., against the will of the south Korean people as railroading the illegal "motion on impeachment against the president" through the NA under the U.S. manipulation and strongly demand them immediately withdraw it.

Functions Held Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- A meeting, a lecture, etc. took place in Democratic Congo from March 13 to 17 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 11th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Speakers at functions said whenever they commemorate the Day of the Sun they remember the noble life of President Kim Il Sung and his immortal exploits with deep emotion, adding that the exploits he performed by founding the immortal Juche idea and indicating to humankind the most correct way of hewing out their destiny would shine long along with human history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great vitality of the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il has been clearly proved by the fact that the DPRK has bravely countered the ceaseless provocation of the imperialists, they noted, and continued: His Songun policy greatly encourages the world progressives desirous of a new independent and peaceful world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting was held under the sponsorship of the General Kim Jong Il Peruvian Amicable Institute on March 18 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the institute said in a speech that Kim Il Sung made an immortal contribution to the cause of global independence as the world recognized and it was his great exploit that he was the first in human history to found the man-centered Juche philosophy and built the most powerful and dignified socialist state in Korea.

Architectural Festival in Pyongyang
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- The Fourth May 21 Architectural Festival, which was opened on March 23 at the People's Palace of Culture, is going on until Friday, the 50th anniversary of the Korean Union of Architects.
 The festival has been visited by a large number of people including local architects and foreigners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, participated in by young dignified and promising architectural designers and technicians from designing institutes and scientific and educational institutions of the architectural field throughout the country, is unprecedented in scale and in the modernization level of designing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented to the festival were more than 300 drafts including "Arirang", "Cradle" and "Fragrance" and some 40 designing programs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival is divided into a prize contest of designs of dwelling houses in towns and rural communities, a prize contest of designs of town and rural districts and a contest of architectural designing programs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the festival have informed each other of and exchanged the achievements and experience they have gained in the efforts for implementing the architectural ideas of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The displays will be estimated through amateurs' consideration, experts' consideration and state consideration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival is an important occasion in further developing the nation's architectural designing to meet the requirements of the new century.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 26 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, inspected KPA Unit 916.
 He was saluted on the spot by the commanding officers of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He acquainted himself with the performance of the unit's duty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at the room devoted to the unit's history, conducted by the commander of the unit. Seeing the records showing the glorious path covered by the unit, he stressed that the unit should lead all the servicepersons to uphold and glorify its fighting tradition. Going round the servicepersons' hall, a military lecture room and a political lecture room, he got familiar in detail with the study of military technology and political and ideological education among the servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the successes made by the officers and men of the unit, greatly pleased to see them trained as one-match-for-a-hundred fighters capable of wiping out any formidable enemy through intensive training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very good to train all soldiers as fighters strong in ideology and faith, he said, adding that the trait of giving importance to ideology is a peculiar feature and tradition of the KPA which has won one victory after another, weathering out tempest of the revolution, with the strength of idea for the last 70 odd year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He advanced highly important tasks which would serve as guidelines in increasing the combat capacity of the unit in every way, greatly satisfied with the great successes the commanding officers and men of the unit have achieved through the vigorous struggle to thoroughly implement the WPK's self-defensive military line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the soldiers' service and living, going round an education room, a library, a bedroom, a mess hall, a washroom, a subsidiary food store, an outdoor resting place, a fish farm and other places of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He spared time to appreciate an art performance given by soldiers of a company under the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Vice Marshal Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA General Staff and member of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, and KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong.
